properties.areaDesc: South Laramie Range Foothills; South Laramie Range; Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 2 at 2:01PM MST until January 5 at 7:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...STRONG WINDS RETURNING TO SOUTHEAST WYOMING FRIDAY INTO THE
WEEKEND...

The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a High Wind
Warning, which is in effect from 5 AM Friday to 7 AM MST Sunday.
The High Wind Watch is no longer in effect.

* WHAT...West winds 40 to 50 mph with gusts up to 75 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County,
North Snowy Range Foothills, South Laramie Range and South
Laramie Range Foothills Counties.

* WHEN...From Friday morning through Sunday morning.

* TIMING...Winds will begin increasing in strength early Friday
morning...with gusts exceeding 60 mph by 5AM.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Travel will be hazardous for
light weight and high profile vehicles, including camping and
tractor trailers. There will be an elevated blow over risk along
Interstate 80 over the summit between Cheyenne and Laramie.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts
of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 5 AM FRIDAY TO 7 AM MST SUNDAY
